      "value": "<p><em>A hulking figure clad in a black armor adorned with thorny ornaments slowly walks forward, seemingly unhindered by the thick vegetation of the surrounding woods.</em><br>Thornheart guardians are unyielding and merciless defenders of the forest domains of hags and other sinister fey. They are the twisted cousins of @UUID[Compendium.koboldpressogl-bf.koboldpressmonsters.Actor.KPgreenknightoft]{green knights of the woods}, and good-aligned fey often send green knights on hunts to destroy thornheart guardians and their creators.<br><strong>Shadow Origins.</strong> Thornheart guardians are created from the bodies and souls of unfortunate knights who foolishly fell for the charms of hags or dark fey and swore eternal servitude to them. In unholy ceremonies, hags fuse the knights’ bodies with armor forged in the Shadow Realm then transform the knights’ hearts into a cluster of enchanted thorns.<br><strong>Relentless and Loyal.</strong> The thornheart guardian is a terror to behold. Once it has found its mark, it doesn’t back down until the enemies of its sinister liege have been slain. Its enchanted heart gives it power over the plants around it, and it uses these plants to capture and kill its enemies.<br><strong>Construct Nature.</strong> The thornheart guardian doesn’t require air, food, drink, or sleep.<br><h2>Alternate Traits and Actions</h2><br>The following changes allow GMs to alter a thornheart guardian without modifying its challenge rating:<br><em><strong>Innate Spellcasting.</strong></em> The thornheart guardian’s innate spellcasting ability is Wisdom (spell save DC 15) It can innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:<br><strong>At will:</strong> <em>entangle, pass without trace, plant growth</em><br><strong>3/day each:</strong> <em>blight, grasping vine, hallucinatory terrain</em><br><strong>1/day each:</strong> <em>transport via plants, wall of thorns</em><br>The thornheart guardian’s Wisdom increases to 16, which increases its Wisdom (Perception) modifier to +7 and its passive Perception to 17. The thornheart guardian loses its Magic Weapons trait.<br><em><strong>Rejuvenation.</strong></em> A thornheart guardian that dies collapses into a pile of thorny vines (or explodes if it has the Thorny Explosion trait). If it dies within a forest, the thornheart guardian reforms from the plants in 1d6 days and regains all its hp. Only removing all traces of the guardian’s body from the forest prevents this trait from functioning.<br>The thornheart guardian’s Grasp of the Briar action reduces its Recharge to 6. If it possesses this trait and the Thorny Explosion trait, it loses its Grasp of the Briar action.<br><em><strong>Thorny Explosion.</strong></em> When it dies, the thornheart guardian explodes in a burst of thorny vines. Each creature within 30 feet of the guardian must make a DC 16 Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes 7 (2d6) slashing damage and 7 (2d6) necrotic damage and is restrained by the vines. On a success, a creature takes half the damage and isn’t restrained. A restrained creature takes 7 (2d6) necrotic damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature, including the restrained target, can take its action to break the target free of the vines by succeeding on a DC 16 Strength check.<br>The thornheart guardian’s Grasp of the Briar action reduces its Recharge to 6. If it possesses this trait and the Rejuvenation trait, it loses its Grasp of the Briar action.<br>Content licensed under the @UUID[Compendium.koboldpressogl-bf.koboldpressjournal.JournalEntry.KoboldPressOGL00.JournalEntryPage.KoboldPressOGLpg]{Open Game License}"
